## Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist

- Never share OTP, PIN, or passwords with anyone
- Do not click on suspicious links or unknown messages
- Always verify the identity of callers claiming to be from banks
- Avoid scanning QR codes from unknown sources
- Do not accept payment requests unless you are sure of the sender
- Regularly check your bank and UPI transaction history
- Use strong and unique passwords for all accounts
- Enable two-factor authentication wherever possible

### UPI Safety Tips
- Remember that receiving money does not require entering a PIN
- Never approve unknown “collect request” notifications

